{\bf Iterative Solver for the Finite Difference Time Domain Method with Application of Thin Film Solar Cell Simulation }}

Martensstraﬂe 3 \\ University Erlangen-Nuremberg \\ Department of Computer Science \\ D-91058 Erlangen
\\
{\tt pflaum@informatik.uni-eralngen.de}\end{center}


To optimize the optical properties of
thin film solar cells it is necessary to simulate the optical properties
of the nanostructure of these solar cells.
The finite difference time domain method for Maxwell¥s equations
is a suitable method for such simulations.
To reduce the computational amount fast iterative solvers are needed.


